Nigeria Premier Football League champions Rivers United have attributed their new found form to unity and togetherness in the squad. The Pride of Rivers have recorded impressive results in the CAF Confederation Cup recently. Stanley Eguma’s side have won their last three games in the competition. Rivers United recorded their latest victory against Daring Club Motema Pembe last Wednesday. “Energy, Unity and Togetherness,”reads a tweet on the club’s official Twitter handle. Rivers United will take on Enugu Rangers in a rescheduled tie on Wednesday.